To our Cabo Bobs Friends, 

Fifteen years ago, we embarked on an extraordinary journey to the heart of Austin, Texas, in order to bring the unique Baja's flavors to our vibrant community. Today, we stand in awe and gratitude as we celebrate this remarkable milestone together. As we look back on the incredible memories and the countless burritos shared, we cannot help but feel immense appreciation for each one of you. Your unwavering support, loyalty, and love for Cabo Bob's Burritos has been the driving force behind our success. From the very beginning, Don and I wanted to create a delicious experience that transcended borders - a taste of Baja's finest, nurtured by Austin's warmth and spirit. Your enthusiasm for our fresh ingredients, handmade tortillas, and authentic flavors has been the fuel that keeps our fires burning. Our journey is far from over, and we could not be more thrilled to have you by our side. Here's to 15 years of great memories and many more to come!

With love and appreciation,
The Cabo Bob's Burritos Family

P.S. Thanks for the Journey!

Oh how times have changed!!!! This is our Ben White store under construction before opening and then today. If you've been to this Cabo Bob's anytime in the last few years, you know this place is normally packed with burrito lovers. 

We could not be more thankful for all of you. Here's to 15 years of serving burritos... and many many more to come. Thanks for the Journey!

Meet Sal Olivas, one of our Rio Grande Managing Partners! 

If you have ever been to our Rio Grande location, you most likely already know and love him. If you haven't, he's the tall guy behind the counter! Originally, Sal moved to Austin to play rugby for the Austin Blacks! He now has worked with Cabo Bobs for about 2 years and has recently traveled to Spain, with his son, to run with the bulls. As you can see, he did not forget to rep his favorite team! 

Thank you so much for everything you do, Sal! We are lucky to have you!
